# Keep the build context lean — anything not strictly needed by the
# Dockerfile stages should be ignored. Smaller context = faster builds
# and no chance of accidentally shipping host artifacts into the image.

# Node / build artifacts (Stage 1 generates them fresh inside the image)
web/node_modules
web/dist

# Go binary outputs
/lemur-pouch
/lemur-pouch.exe

# Per-loop transcripts from scripts/review.sh
.review-logs

# Editor / OS
.DS_Store
.vscode
.idea
*.swp

# Git internals — the Dockerfile doesn't need history. Saves ~tens of MB
# on a long-lived repo and avoids leaking commit metadata into image
# layers via accidental `COPY .` paths.
.git
.gitignore

# Documentation that doesn't belong in the runtime image
*.md
!web/README.md   # exception: web/README.md is referenced by Vite tooling

# CI configuration (irrelevant to the image build)
.github
